Mother’s Day may be over, but I celebrate the title of Mother today — May 12th.
Because exactly two years ago, on this very day, I found out I was going to be a mom.
That moment is forever etched in my heart — the two lines on the pregnancy test, the nervousness, the joy, the overwhelming excitement — all crashing in at once.
Today, I rewind and relive that feeling.

I feel so incredibly blessed to have you, my girl.
Thank you for choosing me as your Mumma. I promise to spoil you endlessly with love and to always be there to fulfill your dreams and little demands.

I love you, my girl. You are the greatest blessing of my life.
